<item>
            <title>[HBASE-4539] OpenedRegionHandler racing with itself in ServerShutDownhandler flow leading to HMaster abort</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-4539</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Steps to reproduce&lt;br/&gt;
==================&lt;br/&gt;
-&amp;gt; Region R1 is being opened in RS1.  &lt;br/&gt;
-&amp;gt;After processing the znode to OPENED RS1 goes down.&lt;br/&gt;
-&amp;gt;Now before the OpenedRegionHandler executor deletes the znode if ServerShutDownHandler tries to assign the region to RS2, RS2 transits the node to OPENED and this OpenedRegionHandler executor deletes the znode.  &lt;br/&gt;
-&amp;gt;Now if the first OpenedRegionHandler tries deleting the znode it throws NoNode Exception and causes the HMaster to abort.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
